newsitem.title: USA: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices steady to lower.
newsitem.headline: U.S. bulk millfeeds - Prices steady to lower.

text.p: Cash millfeed prices ended mostly steady to lower Monday, starting off a week of subdued activity, millfeed dealers said.
One Buffalo dealer said he had expected Monday to be quiet because a lot of feed people in the Northeast had attended a general feed conference in Boston and were just returning to work.
Another broker said the continued cold weather in February in parts of the Midwest should prompt more demand for feed.
"I would say the supply and demand picture is pretty much in equilibrium," a Carolinas dealer said.
In Minnesota, one dealer noted a little bit of demand. "There is very light interest for millfeed in the nearby," he said.
